can restore a total number of 30 hit points. As an action, it can touch a creature and draw power from the pool to restore a number of hit points to that creature, up to the maximum amount remaining in its pool. Alternatively, it can expend 5 hit points from its pool of healing to cure the target of one disease or neutralize one poison affecting it.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Beneos Tokens","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"self","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[["",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"_id":"vDkNWzmE1pYkOBlT","img":"beneos_tokens_assets//_ability_icons/priestskill_44.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"7ptJY7RGU63YcaB9":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.DxzbNivEQXCpAcS5.Item.vDkNWzmE1pYkOBlT"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1667496234460,"modifiedTime":1667983575971,"lastModifiedBy":"HmIGuCna9IfVj3NR"}}],"effects":[],"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"new_test","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.288","systemVersion":"2.0.3"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Actor.MeqPd6UY2l3z3QHI","hash":"7157fdea0341570ff39f0b30fa5aa1f87a6ffe64"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.beneostokens.beneostokens_actors.PjXVwTungqCAFK5s"}},"system":{"abilities":{"str":{"value":18,"proficient":1,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"dex":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"con":{"value":16,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"int":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"wis":{"value":14,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"cha":{"value":18,"proficient":1,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}}},"attributes":{"ac":{"flat":18,"calc":"flat","formula":""},"hp":{"value":69,"min":0,"max":69,"temp":null,"tempmax":0,"formula":"9d8+27"},"init":{"value":0,"bonus":0},"movement":{"burrow":0,"climb":0,"fly":0,"swim":0,"walk":30,"units":"ft","hover":false},"attunement":{"max":3},"senses":{"darkvision":0,"blindsight":0,"tremorsense":0,"truesight":0,"units":"ft","special":""},"spellcasting":"int"},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<h1>How to run a Crusader</h1><div><p></p></div><h3><strong>1. Offensively.</strong></h3><ul><li><p>At the start of the combat encounter, choose your Crusader’s Vow. Start of with Judgement or Beneficence to boost your offensive capabilities and bank on bursting an enemy down to take a second Vow. Ferocity and Fortitude aren’t as contradictory as it seems, as this setup allows to you to charge into combat and stay there.</p><div><p></p></div></li><li><p>To not trouble you as the DM with spell slots or too much ressource management, the Crusader’s Smite equivalent works as a rechargeable ability - Divine Champion.</p><div><p></p></div></li><li><p>Simply put, Declare Challenge is an action, instead of a much more effective bonus action, because of both balance and roleplay reasons. Advantage on two attacks, possibly a third one via Devout Interception, can go a long way maximizing the Crusader’s damage output. It also evokes the right feel - the Crusader does not bellow its challenge and attacks immediately, the opponent must have some time to react to the challenge!</p><div><p></p></div></li><li><p>Devout Interception is no Attack of Opportunity - even if an enemy disengaged, you can move after them or, well, intercept them to attack!</p><div><p></p></div></li><li><p>Remember that every damage roll of 1 or 2 for the Crusader Greatsword counts as a 3. This has already been considered for the average damage, but if you prefer to roll, keep it in mind.</p></li></ul><div><p></p></div><h3><strong>2. Defensively.</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Spiritual Fortitude acts as mini-Legendary Resistance. It does not always work, but a 50/50 chance to resist a devastating save that you’ve already failed is nothing to sniff at!</p><div><p></p></div></li><li><p>Purify Body and Soul is as straightforward as it gets - use an action to heal yourself</p><div><p></p></div></li></ul><h3><strong>3. General Notes</strong></h3><div><p></p></div><ul><li><p>Declare your challenge, get into melee and start hacking. It feels really nice to just go ham with an especially angry Paladin!</p><div><p></p></div></li><li><p>Note that they are not good aligned - a heavily armed zealot backed by divine power is morally grey at best and should act accordingly.</p></li></ul>","public":""},"alignment":"Neutral","race":"","type":{"value":"humanoid","subtype":"","swarm":"","custom":""},"environment":"","cr":5,"spellLevel":0,"xp":{"value":10},"source":"Beneos Tokens"},"traits":{"size":"med","di":{"value":[],"bypasses":[],"custom":""},"dr":{"value":[],"bypasses":[],"custom":""},"dv":{"value":[],"bypasses":[],"custom":""},"ci":{"value":[],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":["common"],"custom":""}},"currency":{"pp":0,"gp":0,"ep":0,"sp":0,"cp":0},"skills":{"acr":{"value":0,"ability":"dex","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""}},"ani":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""}},"arc":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""}},"ath":{"value":1,"ability":"str","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""}},"dec":{"value":0,"ability":"cha","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""}},"his":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""}},"ins":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""}},"itm":{"value":0,"ability":"cha","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""}},"inv":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonuses":{"check":"","passive":""}},"med":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonuses"