erit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Blood Mist.</strong> Red, iron-scented blood mist spreads from a point Sharakhul chooses within 60 feet of him, filling a 15-foot-radius sphere. The area is heavily obscured until the dragon dismisses it as a bonus action, uses this lair action again, or dies. The blood mist spreads around corners. Each enemy creature that is completely within the cloud at the start of its turn must make a DC 17 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the creature spends its action that turn choking, gagging and heaving. Creatures that don’t need to breathe automatically succeed on this saving throw.</span></p></li></ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Beneos Tokens","activation":{"type":"lair","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":60,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":17,"scaling":"flat"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"_id":"3TjEnHoPXodEBZbN","img":"beneos_tokens_assets//_ability_icons/40.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0,"7ptJY7RGU63YcaB9":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.HrzuHaPEWhNqQn9b.Item.3TjEnHoPXodEBZbN"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666978636233,"modifiedTime":1666980989268,"lastModifiedBy":"7ptJY7RGU63YcaB9"}},{"name":"Painful Memories","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<ul><li><p><strong>Painful Memories.</strong> Sharakhul the Flayed is in constant pain, as his body is as broken as his mind. His lair is steeped in pain, both his and that of his victims. Just looking at his flayed form can be enough to cause nausea in hardened adventurers, but the true horror lies in the gift of telepathy that was forced upon him by his tentacled torturers. Every creature within 60 ft. of Sharakhul must succeed on a DC 17 Charisma saving throw or be influenced by the vile echoes of torture haunting this place. Each time an affected creature takes damage, it takes an additional 6 (1d10) psychic damage.</p></li></ul><p><br /></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Beneos Tokens","activation":{"type":"lair","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":60,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"cha","dc":17,"scaling":"flat"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"_id":"wn7nmajVSeyVrSl7","img":"beneos_tokens_assets//_ability_icons/skill_275_nobg.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0,"7ptJY7RGU63YcaB9":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.HrzuHaPEWhNqQn9b.Item.wn7nmajVSeyVrSl7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666978636367,"modifiedTime":1666981315901,"lastModifiedBy":"7ptJY7RGU63YcaB9"}},{"name":"Boiling Blood Pits","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<ul><li><strong>Boiling Blood Pits.</strong> Sharakhul’s lair contains several 15-foot-radius pits carved into the ground, each big enough to fully contain his massive form. Within these holes are bubbling pools of ever-boiling blood. Each day, Sharakhul subermerges himself within in a futile attempt to boil away the constant pain wracking his tortured frame. As a lair action the pits erupt, raining down boiling blood within the lair. Each creature within 50 ft. of a pool must succeed on a DC 17 Dexterity saving throw or suffer 21 (6d6) fire damage or half as much on a success.</li></ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Beneos Tokens","activation":{"type":"lair","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":50,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[["6d6","fire"]],"versatile":"21"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":17,"scaling":"flat"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"_id":"ikeyp7ilmno8Ktzz","img":"beneos_tokens_assets//_ability_icons/red_21.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"7ptJY7RGU63YcaB9":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.HrzuHaPEWhNqQn9b.Item.ikeyp7ilmno8Ktzz"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1666978636511,"modifiedTime":1666981215725,"lastModifiedBy":"7ptJY7RGU63YcaB9"}}],"effects":[],"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"new_test","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"10.288","systemVersion":"2.0.3"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Actor.lByyHGZ9hsregKCs","hash":"0af830b062fc527487ced32a618b75b7663f35a9"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.beneostokens.beneostokens_actors.ybnKGtRPKIsLkzo6"}},"system":{"abilities":{"str":{"value":25,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"dex":{"value":12,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"con":{"value":22,"proficient":1,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"int":{"value":20,"proficient":0,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"wis":{"value":16,"proficient":1,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}},"cha":{"value":18,"proficient":1,"bonuses":{"check":"","save":""}}},"attributes":{"ac":{"flat":18,"calc":"natural","formula":""},"hp":{"value":180,"min":0,"max":180,"temp":120,"tempmax":0,"formula":"15d12+90"},"init":{"value":0,"bonus":0},"movement":{"burrow":0,"climb":0,"fly":60,"swim":0,"walk":40,"units":"ft","hover":false},"attunement":{"max":3},"senses":{"darkvision":60,"blindsight":0,"tremorsense":0,"truesight":0,"units":"ft","special":"passive Perception 25"},"spellcasting":"int"},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"page\" id=\"p7\"><div class=\"columnWrapper\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;max-height:100%;column-span:all;columns:inherit;column-gap:inherit\"><h1 id=\"how-to-run-sharakhul-the-flayed\" style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:0.89cm;line-height:1em;font-family:MrEavesRemake;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px 0px 0.18cm;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:var(--HB_Color_HeaderText);column-span:all\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">How to run Sharakhul the Flayed</strong></span></h1><h5 id=\"a-guide-on-how-to-terrorize-your-party-with-the-skinless-scourge-of-harrowspire\" style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:900;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:0.423cm;line-height:0.951em;font-family:ScalySansSmallCapsRemake;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><em style=\"border:0px;font-style:italic;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact\"><strong>A Guide on how to terrorize your party with the Skinless Scourge of Harrowspire</strong></em></span></h5><h3 id=\"1-overview\" style=\"border-top:0px;border-right:0px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--HB_Color_HeaderUnderline);border-left:0px;border-image:initial;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:0.575cm;line-height:0.995em;font-family:MrEavesRemake;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0.2cm 0px 0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:var(--HB_Color_HeaderText)\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">1. Overview</strong></span></h3><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div><ul style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px 0px 0.8em;padding:0px 0px 0px 1.4em;list-style:outside disc;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact\"><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\">Sharakhul is a gargantuan dragon, but he is a bit more frail in comparison to other dragons of his size. Due to his lack of scales, his AC is only 18 and he only has 180 hit points. He compensates for this by his use of the Red Kin (see: <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Host of the Red Kin</strong>). This feature effectively boosts his hit points to 300, with the ability to regain Red Kin (see: <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Devour</strong>).</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\">The Flayed Dragon is a complex monster to run. <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Tainted Blood, Splintered Mind, Host of the Red Kin</strong> and <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Devour</strong> are all abilities that require some bookkeeping and attention to detail. To balance this, his actions, reactions and legendary actions and lair actions are relatively straightforward.</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li></ul><h3 id=\"2-mechanics-and-abilities\" style=\"border-top:0px;border-right:0px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--HB_Color_HeaderUnderline);border-left:0px;border-image:initial;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:0.575cm;line-height:0.995em;font-family:MrEavesRemake;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0.155cm 0px 0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:var(--HB_Color_HeaderText)\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">2. Mechanics and Abilities</strong></span></h3><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div><ul style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px 0px 0.8em;padding:0px 0px 0px 1.4em;list-style:outside disc;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact\"><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Splintered Mind:</strong> Always keep the secondary effect of this ability in mind when Sharakhul becomes the target of a spell. There are quite a lot of spells (or abilities for that matter) that establish or require some kind of psychic connection. Linking with Sharakhuls unhinged psyche invites punishment.</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Tainted Blood:</strong> This ability forces the party to make some hard decisions regarding when to deal damage and when to hold back, as melee classes will be covered in Sharakhul’s blood most of the time.</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Host of the Red Kin:</strong> Sharakhul usually starts the fight with six Red Kin, but you can adjust the difficulty by adding more or removing some, if you are so inclined. Each Red Kin has 20 hit points and if one is destroyed, the extra damage damages Sharakhul himself, even if he still has kin. If an attack deals 30 damage, it destroys one Kin and deals 10 damage to Sharakhul directly, next instance of damage however is absorbed by the next Red Kin. You could always run Sharakhul with some support and it is completely in line with his character to <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Devour</strong> an ally to absorb it and get another Kin.</span></p></li></ul><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div><h3 id=\"3-actions\" style=\"border-top:0px;border-right:0px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--HB_Color_HeaderUnderline);border-left:0px;border-image:initial;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:0.575cm;line-height:0.995em;font-family:MrEavesRemake;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:var(--HB_Color_HeaderText)\"><span style=\"font-family:MrEavesRemake\"><strong>3. Actions</strong></span></h3><ul style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0.17cm 0px 0.8em;padding:0px 0px 0px 1.4em;list-style:outside disc;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact\"><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Devour</strong>: One of the factors making Sharakhul very lethal, as he damages a creature and parallely effectively removes it from combat. A balancing factor is that is is relatively easy to escape from within him as more creatures are swallowed, as the damage necessary to force a saving throw does not have to be dealt by a single creature on its turn - swallowed creatures have to deal 30 points of cumulative damage. They are however blinded and restrained, so its not <em style=\"border:0px;font-style:italic;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact\">too</em> easy and keeping up to six creatures down his throat for another turn might be a Legendary Resistance well spent.</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Talons</strong>: The Talons by themselves are nothing to write home about, but combined with either <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Psychic Flaying</strong> or <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Painful Presence</strong> these two Talon attacks per turn can be devastating.</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Tail</strong>: Both Tail options add some versatility to Sharakhul’s moveset and aim to keep players on their toes. Grappling a creature with a <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Slam</strong> attack can also serve the purpose of removing it from greater danger - if you want to keep the party’s healer safe from an impending <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Psychic Flaying</strong> but don’t want to be too obvious about it, grapple it with the tail. It’s still a chunk of damage, but now the character is on the wrong end of the dragon to be hit by other stuff.</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Painful Presence</strong>: Usually Dragons have some kind of fear effect, but not Sharakhul. This is another of his most deadly features and can set the stage for a devastating barrage of Legendary Actions. A <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Painful Presence</strong> followed by a series of <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Tail (Gore</strong>) Legendary Actions can put a dent in almost everything. It’s also a great way to boost the efficiency of otherwise neglectable minions, as even less powerful attacks hurt when they deal double damage.</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Psychic Flaying</strong>: Instead of a breath weapon, Sharakhul has his Psychic Flaying action. Now this deals less damage than an ancient dragon’s breath, but, again, being vulnerable to <em style=\"border:0px;font-style:italic;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact\">all</em> damage types is a big deal. This does not stack with his <strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Tainted Blood</strong>, as psychic damage is mercifully excluded.</span></p></li></ul><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"></p></div></div><div class=\"page\" id=\"p8\"><div class=\"columnWrapper\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;max-height:100%;column-span:all;columns:inherit;column-gap:inherit\"><ul style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px 0px 0.8em;padding:0px 0px 0px 1.4em;list-style:outside disc;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact\"><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Mindscream</strong>: This ability can break a party, as it might deprive them of their most powerful caster. However, a high level party should have access to a greater restoration or heal effect, but its a great way to force some resource spending. This ability can straight up remove a character from combat and can also be used as a signal to your players to get the hell out of there and return with more knowledge and prep time. It is limited to two uses per day though and will probably fail to achieve anything if you put too much hope into it.</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Skinless Shroud</strong>: If compared to our regular dragon, the reaction section lacks some damage and mobility options. But Sharakhul has enough going on and he is a bit on the frail side and can only half some damage and not negate it outright. His tattered wings also cause him to be not as swift as his healthier brethren, so he has no means of disenganging per reaction, bonus action or legendary action. But given that a melee attack can douse you in tainted dragon blood, maybe it is better to let him get out of melee range unscathed.</span></p><div class=\"blank\" style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:1em\"><p></p></div></li><li style=\"border:0px;font:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;break-inside:avoid\"><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><strong style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:bold;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Legendary Actions</strong>: Sharakhul can take three legendary actions per round, one allows him to make some additional attacks and two give the Red Kin something to do, applying either the grappled or frightened condition.</span></p></li></ul><h3 id=\"4-conclusion\" style=\"border-top:0px;border-right:0px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--HB_Color_HeaderUnderline);border-left:0px;border-image:initial;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:0.575cm;line-height:0.995em;font-family:MrEavesRemake;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0.155cm 0px 0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:var(--HB_Color_HeaderText)\"><span style=\"font-family:MrEavesRemake\"><strong>4. Conclusion</strong></span></h3><p style=\"border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.25em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0.17cm 0px 0px;padding:0px;box-sizing:border-box;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;overflow-wrap:break-word;display:block\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\">Keep track of devoured and tainted characters, as well as the number of Red Kin left. Sharakhul’s modus operandi is to overwhelm his enemies, tearing into them while shrieking continously and then use their panic to pick them off one by one. You should try the same - keep him on the offensive and should he get cornered, use one of his abilities to sow fear and regain the upper hand. Don’t pick fights with characters that have ways to mitigate his insane damage output or use his lack of mobility against him, always try to force the players to react and adapt to his next horrible ability.</span></p></div></div>","public":""},"alignment":"Chaotic Evil","race":"","type":{"value":"dragon","subtype":"","swarm":"","custom":""},"environment":"","cr":20,"spellLevel":0,"xp":{"value":10},"source":"Beneos Tokens"},"traits":{"size":"grg","di":{"value":[],"bypasses":[],"custom":""},"dr":{"value":[],"bypasses":[],"custom":""},"dv":{"value":[],"bypasses":[],"custom":""