unter that strikes to greatest effect when it gets the drop on its prey. At first it should not try to focus on one player, but rather create an opportunity where vulnerable members of a party can be reached. The combination of Feasting On Fear and the Scything Claws’ bleed effect, paired with the combat prowess of the Spawn all but guarantees it’s regenerative ability to kick in with minimal set up.</p><div><p></p></div><p>The spawn should attack and withdraw before the party gets to mount a coordinated defense - once the Spawn is cornered by close-combat fighters with high AC and hit points, while getting bombarded with spells or arrows from a distance it’s over. It may get some good hits in, but the general oppressive and threatening atmosphere of the encounter will be gone. Both the Blood-Freezing Howl and the Bite are handy tools to prevent the players from ganging up on the Spawn. It not only allows the Spawn to remove a party member from combat by paralyzing them, but enables it to abduct a player before retreating back into whatever nightmarish crypt it emerged from. The fight turns into a chase, as the monster uses its superior speed and maneuverability to retreat from a losing fight, having found a victim to feed on. Only when cornered and cut off from possible escape routes, the Spawn will fight to the death and try to brutally maim as many opponents as possible, ending his reign of terror at the apex of a last sanguine bacchanalia.</p>","public":""},"alignment":"Chaotic Evil","race":"","type":{"value":"undead","subtype":"Vampire","swarm":"","custom":""},"environment":"","cr":6,"spellLevel":0,"xp":{"value":10},"source":"Beneos Tokens"},"traits":{"size":"lg","di":{"value":[],"bypasses":[],"custom":""},"dr":{"value":["bludgeoning","necrotic","piercing","slashing"],"bypasses":["mgc"],"custom":""},"dv":{"value":[],"bypasses":[],"custom":""},"ci":{"value":[],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":"Understands the languages it knew in life, but can’t spe